OPEN: AI will always be biased by whoever programmed it. If we were talking about AI assisted surgery, I'd say that bias is probably a good thing, because the goal of the manufacturers, programmers, sales people and medical professionals is to have a good surgical outcome. Some like the amount of blockage in an artery can be measured, and there's not going to be much difference in opinion about such a thing. AI systems that collect news stories are going to collect all kinds of fake and biased news. Having "the majority of sources" say one thing or another means absolutely nothing, as far as the truth is concerned. On the other hand, having ONE source that is constantly edited by the public can be extrodinarily accurate, as Wikipedia has proven. The "wisdom of the crowd" theory works, but only when real people are controlling it.
